metadata.name: Planet Panels #147
metadata.description:
Stylised isometric terrain with a shifting hand-drawn aesthetic. 

Press any key to toggle black background.

Fully deterministic but the higher your viewport the more terrain will be drawn, this is preferable to fixed scaling.

metadata.name: Signals #100
metadata.description: Signals capture the pulsar signals generated by the dying stars at the time of minting.  At this moment in time, the color attributes of the original star are detected and captured in the signal plot.

metadata.name: overloaded #290
metadata.description: Overloaded attempts to be a system to explore time perception, through non-representative images, while still representing pixels as upscaled forms. It plays with permanence and non-permanence.

metadata.name: Aeoflu #404
metadata.description:
This broadcast is transmitted to the brains of the humanoid race from the planet Xiurq during hyperspace travel. The algorithm is specifically designed to preserve the cognitive functions of the species during "slow time" and overload. The use of the algorithm by other races has not been studied. Prohibited for use outside specially certified laboratories by intergalactic convention 30292-HD-92 

The idea of this project is infinite motion, but it can be stopped (“space”) and save static image ("s" button)

There are three modes. They are switched by click. Each switch changes the input parameters, so there are quite a few options

!!!Flashing lights seizure warning!!!

metadata.name: PARIS #41
metadata.description:
Paris is a generative and animated piece creating shapes based on trails. 
The size, position and motion frequency of each circles are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Each reloading creates a different movement, as the algorithm underlying the piece is partially based on a noise.
At the end, the animation stop and the visual is created.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in La-Roche-Neuville (France).

metadata.name: sinuosity #149
metadata.description:
sinuosity is defined as:

- (n.) the ability to curve or bend easily and flexibly.

sinuous is defined as a couple of things:

- (adj.) having many curves and turns.
- (adj.) lithe and supple.

each curve anchors to the center. 

maybe that center is a life. (maybe that center is you.)

maybe that curve is a relationship. (or a job.) (or repressed trauma that needs processing.)

maybe that curve has other curves within. (it probably does.)

sometimes there are many curves at once. (usually this the case.) 

occasionally, there may only be one. (life isn’t always so complicated.) 

whatever curves the moment contains it can help to step away and see how they come together. (this is not always easy.)

[cc0] [p5js] [xoxo] [twitter: @heyjeres]

metadata.name: De/FragV3 #67
metadata.description: The 3rd piece in this series is a painterly interpretation of De/FragV2 and highlighting more temporal aspects of the underlying algorithms (Voronoi & Jump Flooding) in unique and never repeating sequences.

metadata.name: Skravert #224
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: Hexaëder #117
metadata.description:
Hexaëder (cube) is a research into abstraction and a search for a balance between simplification and visual complexity.

No matter how simple and unambiguous things appear to be, in reality they are often more complex. Enjoy the simple, explore the complex.

Hexaeder has a wide variety of possible outcomes. I have put together 10 different color palettes; the number of cubes ranges from 10 to 401 (18 different grids); each cell can have 4 different background patterns; each cube can be filled in 4 distinct ways; there are 5 line colors and 16 different "cube figures"; the vignette can be black or be the color of the palette, and there are several "texture settings". This results in over 1.8 million possibilities.

For more information see: https://www.behance.net/gallery/131114761/Hexaeder-Flattened-cubes

metadata.name: Protein Pelt #96
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.
